---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for Craft-Supply Stores in 2026';
const description = 'A practical shortlist of Shopify email apps for craft supplies, project education, replenishment, kits, launches, and customer retention.';
const apps = [['Sequenzy','Education-led craft businesses','Good for project guides, kit onboarding, and complementary-supply journeys.','Project and catalog integrations should be confirmed.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Klaviyo','Craft catalogs with detailed project data','Useful for craft, project, purchase, and engagement segmentation.','Large catalogs and compatibility rules need governance.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Craft retailers scaling ecommerce','A practical fit for kits, browse, cart, launches, and replenishment.','Product compatibility and promotion logic need QA.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/automations/'],['Brevo','Content and lifecycle craft brands','Useful when tutorials and automation share a broader platform.','Product taxonomy mapping may require connectors.','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small craft catalogs','A simple native option for kit launches and tutorials.','Less suited to complex compatibility branches.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing'],['Drip','Craft stores building project-led repeat purchase','Commerce automation can connect kit purchases to supplies and replenishment.','Project relationships and inventory events need accurate modeling.','https://www.drip.com/features'],['Mailchimp','Craft retailers with a tutorial newsletter','Campaigns support project ideas, seasonal collections, and maker education.','Deep kit-completion or compatibility logic may require extra work.','https://mailchimp.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['ActiveCampaign','Stores combining project nurture with CRM follow-up','Branching workflows can coordinate education, support, and purchase milestones.','More operational complexity for a small catalog.','https://www.activecampaign.com/marketing-automation'],['Customer.io','Technical craft brands with event-rich project data','Event-driven messages fit kit views, tutorial milestones, and replenishment events.','Event taxonomy must distinguish ownership from interest.','https://customer.io/product'],['Sendlane','Growing craft stores prioritizing ecommerce triggers','Commerce workflows cover browse, cart, post-purchase, and cross-sell.','Confirm catalog and project-event integrations.','https://www.sendlane.com/features'],['MailerLite','Small stores sending accessible project content','A simple editor covers welcome, guides, launches, and basic follow-up.','Fewer advanced compatibility branches.','https://www.mailerlite.com/features'],['ConvertKit','Creator-led craft businesses teaching techniques','Tag-based sequences fit tutorials, workshops, and maker storytelling.','Retail catalog automation is lighter.','https://convertkit.com/features'],['GetResponse','Craft stores growing guide downloads and waitlists','Forms and automation support project lead magnets and kit launches.','Broader funnel tools add setup choices.','https://www.getresponse.com/features'],['AWeber','Small teams sending dependable project updates','Straightforward broadcasts and autoresponders cover a compact lifecycle.','Limited product-level recommendation controls.','https://www.aweber.com/features.htm']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Craft-supply customers often buy toward a project. Email can be more useful when it connects supplies, instruction, skill level, and the next step instead of listing unrelated products.</p><p>Measure project-kit conversion, complementary attach rate, tutorial engagement, replenishment, and returns. Keep compatibility guidance accurate and use purchase history to avoid recommending supplies the customer already has.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for craft supplies</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[0]} is useful when project or compatibility context changes the recommendation, onboarding, or replenishment path. Build education around a customer’s purchased kit or stated interest, then use a clear milestone before asking for the next purchase. Practical guidance is a stronger retention asset than generic promotional volume.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Review current contacts, sends, automation, catalog, and event limits; tutorials and project data may add event volume.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Need</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Project fit</td><td>Compatibility and kit context</td><td>Attach rate</td></tr><tr><td>Education</td><td>Tutorial and milestone events</td><td>Engagement and completion</td></tr><tr><td>Retention</td><td>Supply cadence and purchase state</td><td>Repeat purchase</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Read <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, explore <a href="/use-cases/product-education">product education</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
